article.description: John Walton III had 22 points, hauled in a career-high 19 rebounds and Troy held off a second-half Paine rally for an 85-77 win Thursday night.
article.headline: Troy holds off Paine for 85-77 win
article.linkText: Troy holds off Paine for 85-77 win
article.story: DOTHAN, Ala. -- John Walton III had 22 points, hauled in a career-high 19 rebounds and Troy held off a second-half Paine rally for an 85-77 win Thursday night. Wesley Person scored 28 points, including six 3-pointers, and Jordon Varnado added 16 points for Troy (5-5), which controlled the boards 42-35 to snap a two-game skid. Walton's rebounds fell just one shy of Troy's single-game Division I record. The Trojans took a 46-28 advantage into the break but had to hold off a second half rally to clinch the win. Paine, a Division II program, chipped away at the gap throughout the second half, tying at 71 on a 3-point play from Christian Nobles with 3:56 to play. Troy edged back into the lead with Person's layup, which sparked a 6-0 spurt and the Trojans hung on. Denzel Dillingham's 19 points led three Paine players in double figures.
